Definition 3.5 (Categorical classifying space). Let $G$ a topological monoid group like, define the category $\mathbf{BG}$ as follows: â€¢ Objects are cofibrant $G$-spaces equivalent to $G$ (in the projective model structure $\widehat{\mathbf{G}}$). â€¢ Morphisms are $G$-maps $f:X\rightarrow Y$ which are weak equivalence.
Definition 2.3. (M-principle bundle) Let $X$ be a space and $\mathbf{M}$ a simplicial category with one object $\ast$ i.e., it is equivalent to give a simplicial monoid $M=\mathbf{M}(\ast,\ast)$ of endomorphisms. We call $M$-principle bundle any object $f:E\rightarrow X$ of $\mathbf{Ext}_{\mathbf{M}}(M,X)$ such that $f$ is a fibration of spaces.
Definition 3.3 ($G$-space). A $G$-space $X$ is a topological space with a continues action of $G$.
Definition 2.2. Let $X$ a trivial object of $\widehat{\mathbf{C}}$ and $F$ be any objects of $\widehat{\mathbf{C}}$, define a new category $\mathbf{Ext}_{\mathbf{C}}(F,X)$, where objets are maps $E\rightarrow X$ in $\widehat{\mathbf{C}}$, such that the homotopy pullback $\mathrm{holim}(\ast\rightarrow X\leftarrow E)$ is equivalent to $F$. Morphisms are commutative diagrams: $\xymatrix{E\ar[rr]^{-}{f}_{\sim}\ar[dr]&&E^{{}^{\prime}}\ar[dl]\\ &X&}$ where $f:E\rightarrow E^{{}^{\prime}}$ is a weak equivalence in $\widehat{\mathbf{C}}$.
Definition 2.5. Let $\mathbf{M}$ a model category and $X\in\mathbf{M}$ any object, define $\mathbf{M}_{X}^{we}$ to be the subcategory of $\mathbf{M}$ whose objects are equivalent to $X$ and morphisms are weak equivalences.
